concept_explanation.custom_spans:
**Creating custom spans for business operations:**

```java
import io.micrometer.tracing.Tracer;
import io.micrometer.tracing.Span;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

@Service
public class TradeService {
    private final Tracer tracer;
    private final MarketServiceClient marketClient;

    TradeService(Tracer tracer, MarketServiceClient marketClient) {
        this.tracer = tracer;
        this.marketClient = marketClient;
    }

    public TradeResult executeTrade(String userId, String symbol, int qty) {
        // Create a custom span for the business operation:
        Span span = tracer.nextSpan().name("execute-trade")
            .tag("symbol", symbol)
            .tag("userId", userId)
            .tag("qty", String.valueOf(qty))
            .start();

        try (Tracer.SpanInScope ignored = tracer.withSpan(span)) {
            // Everything inside this block is part of the span:
            StockQuote quote = marketClient.getQuote(symbol);  // creates child span
            double total = quote.price() * qty;

            // Add events to the span:
            span.event("quote-fetched")
                .tag("price", String.valueOf(quote.price()));

            TradeResult result = saveOrder(userId, symbol, qty, total);
            span.event("order-saved");
            return result;

        } catch (Exception e) {
            span.error(e);
            throw e;
        } finally {
            span.end();  // always end the span!
        }
    }
}
```

In Zipkin: 'execute-trade' span appears with symbol/userId/qty tags. Drill into it to see the child spans (marketClient.getQuote, saveOrder).

concept_explanation.baggage:
**Baggage — propagate values across the entire trace:**

```java
import io.micrometer.tracing.Tracer;
import io.micrometer.tracing.propagation.Propagator;

// In a filter or interceptor — set baggage at the entry point:
@Component
public class RequestContextFilter implements Filter {
    private final Tracer tracer;
    RequestContextFilter(Tracer tracer) { this.tracer = tracer; }

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain)
            throws IOException, ServletException {
        // Put userId in baggage — propagates to ALL downstream services:
        // (requires spring.cloud.sleuth.baggage.remote-fields=userId in older versions)
        // In Micrometer Tracing, use MDC:
        String userId = ((HttpServletRequest)req).getHeader("X-User-Id");
        if (userId != null) MDC.put("userId", userId);

        try { chain.doFilter(req, res); }
        finally { MDC.remove("userId"); }
    }
}

// Now log patterns include userId:
logging.pattern.console=%d{HH:mm} [%X{traceId}] userId=%X{userId} %msg%n

// Every service in the trace can log:
// 10:15:32 [abc123] userId=U001 Trade executed
// 10:15:32 [abc123] userId=U001 Payment charged
```

step_by_step_solution.details:
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/stocks")
public class StockController {
    private final Tracer tracer;
    private final StockRepository repo;

    StockController(Tracer tracer, StockRepository repo) {
        this.tracer = tracer; this.repo = repo;
    }

    @GetMapping("/{symbol}/quote")
    public StockQuote getQuote(@PathVariable String symbol) {
        // Custom span for the DB query:
        Span dbSpan = tracer.nextSpan().name("stock-db-query")
            .tag("symbol", symbol).start();

        try (Tracer.SpanInScope s = tracer.withSpan(dbSpan)) {
            // Simulate slow DB query:
            Stock stock = repo.findBySymbol(symbol);
            return new StockQuote(symbol, stock.price(), stock.tradeable());
        } finally {
            dbSpan.end();
        }
    }
}
```

